		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_BUILDING_COUNTY_COURT">
			<TEXT>
				County Court
			</TEXT>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_BUILDING_COUNTY_COURT_HELP">
			<TEXT>
				The County Court adds 2 [ICON_HAPPINESS_1] Happiness in the city which it is built.
			</TEXT>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_BUILDING_COUNTY_COURT_STRATEGY">
			<TEXT>
				The County Court is a judicial building that raises the [ICON_HAPPINESS_1] Happiness of a city.
			</TEXT>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_BUILDING_COUNTY_COURT_DESC">
			<Text>In England and throughout Europe law became increasingly secular as the monarch asserted greater authority on legal matters. In some states this embodied a high court and many smaller courts that would travel throughout the counties. These smaller courts enabled the local populace to bypass the local feudal courts of the nobility and seek a fairer trial at a royal court. Overtime this strangthened the monarch's position, increased the political involvement of the population, and reaffirmed a strong rule of law.</Text>
		</Row>


		<Row Tag="TXT_KEY_BUILDING_ARENA">
